 ethnographic, survey, and interview data in two racially diverse, low-achieving high schools, Warikoo analyzes seemingly oppositional styles, tastes in music, and school behaviors and finds that most teens try to find a balance between success with peers and success in school.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aAcademic achievementvCross-cultural studies. 0aAssimilation (Sociology). 0aChildren of immigrantsvCross-cultural studies. 0aGroup identityvCross-cultural studies. 0aHigh school studentsxSocial life and customsvCross-cultural studies. 0aYouthxSocial life and customsvCross-cultural studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aadministrators.  abehavioral problems.  aclothing.  aethnographers.  aethnography.  aglobalism.  ahigh school students.  ahip hop culture.  aimmigrant experiences.  aimmigrant parents.  aimmigrants.  ainterviews.  alondon.  alow achieving high schools.  aminority students.  amusical tastes.  anew york city.  aparents and kids.  apeer groups.  aracial diversity.  arap culture.  aschool setting.  aschool success.  asurvey data.  ateachers and students.  aurban setting.  ayouth culture.  ayouth music.  ayouths.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052026211940uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094779540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520947795423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520947795/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY